OL,3,CMum, 88, 'terrified' for future of
OL,4,Cdisabled daughter's care
OL,6,FITV Granada Reports correspondent
OL,7,FElaine Wilcox spoke to Anne and Louise
OL,8,Fat their home in Bolton.
OL,10,FAn 88-year-old mother and full-time
OL,11,Fcarer says she is loses sleep over the
OL,12,F"terrifying" prospect of what could
OL,13,Fhappen to her disabled daughter when
OL,14,Fshe can no longer care for her.
OL,16,FAnne Dixon, from Bolton, Greater
OL,17,FManchester, is the main carer for her
OL,18,F63-year-old daughter Louise, who lives
OL,19,Fwith cerebral palsy.
