OL,3,CMum, 88, 'terrified' for future of
OL,4,Cdisabled daughter's care
OL,6,FAnne, who became her primary carer
OL,7,Feight years ago after the death of
OL,8,FLousie's father, says she is worried
OL,9,Fabout her daughter's future when she
OL,10,Fis no longer here because there is
OL,11,Fcurrently "no support" in place.
OL,13,FShe said: "I am worried about what she
OL,14,Fwill do when I'm not there and it has
OL,15,Fto be faced hasn't it? It's something
OL,16,Fa lot of families will have to think
OL,17,Fabout...there's no help except for my
OL,18,Ffriends."
